This paper is about developing a new model for spoken dialogue systems that can handle uncertainty. The paper discusses the use of stochastic models like Markov decision process (MDP) and partially observable Markov decision process (POMDP) for dialogue management. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the arXiv sub-categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of Bayesian networks for extracting low-level information from different input modals, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of Sound (cs.SD) and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC).
